travelerPickup.additionalInfo:
⭐ Meeting point: at port gate (Nha Rong, Hiep Phuoc, Phu Huu, or Phu My port)
⭐ Port Permit Service:
 1. Opt to purchase port permit service: For a fee of 25USD/person, our guide and transport can go inside the port, right to your cruise ship for pick-up and drop off. This requires passport details such as full name, passport number, DOB, expiry date and nationality. We recommend this service for safety and comfort during the hot or rainy days, as well a reliable transport service.
 2. Opt not to purchase port service fee: Please walk out of the port for 7 minutes – 15 minutes or take a shuttle bus inside port gate where our guide and driver will welcome you with a sign and a smile. This does not include a fee.

products.description:
With the brand name of bustle and hustle center in Asia, Ho Chi Minh City is charmed with plenty of shopping malls, souvenir shops, and traditional art showrooms. Explore all of them by joining this Ho Chi Minh City day tour from Phu My port, or Nha Rong, Hiep Phuoc, Phu Huu port.

⭐ HIGHLIGHTS:

 - Go shopping like locals,
 - Best things, best prices, various choices;
 - Hustle and bustle city;
 - Enjoy lunch with Vietnamese traditional food as Vietnamese pancake & rice noodles with grilled pork/fried roll or Pho– specialty food of the city

⭐ Meeting point: port gate outside. (inside optional) 

⭐ Duration: This private tour is approximately 8 hours or longer depending on your time constraints. At the end of the private tour, we always make sure that you return on-time to board the cruise ship.

⭐Tour customizable: Absolutely! (Tell us your specific requirements in the special request form)

itineraryItems.description: Welcome to Ho Chi Minh! Our team will be waiting with name signs, big smiles at your port to take you to your cool air-conditioned transport.

We start our Ho Chi Minh Shore Excursions and visit a local Lacquerware shop. Get a glimpse of this ancient art form by witnessing every detailed step of the manufacturing process under the guidance of local artisans.
Then, head to the XQ showroom where you can admire how embroidery was made. Gazed at a high quality of artistic embroidery designed with traditional Vietnamese images such as lotus, home-dwelling animals, flowers, landscapes, and so on. Moreover, you have a chance to pick up some unique products as gifts and souvenirs for your friends and family.
The next stop is in Sai Gon Square. The center contains a huge scale of retailers and Mercian selling local goods from food, snacks, and fruits to clothing. Most of them are prepared for export that you can purchase some interesting items with reasonable prices. Remember to bargain before deciding to buy anything.
After a delicious meal sampling Pho – Vietnamese traditional noodle soup and spring rolls.
After that, visit Ben Thanh Market – the most famous and bustling market in Ho Chi Minh City. Witness the sight of various stalls full with interesting products from traditional to modern as well as Vietnamese and other countries cuisines. Continue on to the most modern center of the city – Vincom Center Shopping Mall where you enjoy a stroll along hundreds of department stores. The trip ends with a drive back to port.
Trip ends when the driver drops you at the port for the next departure.

products.description:
This tour is for those who always want to know more about the place where they visit, walk through the streets of the historic center and discover the corners and stories that exist in this city.
The historical sites that you will visit are emblematic of the state and are all concentrated in a few streets, without a doubt it is a tour that you will not want to miss.
Bring your most comfortable shoes and a great desire to learn.

itineraryItems.description: Visit the beautiful Metropolitan Cathedral of Guadalajara and learn about its history, the most emblematic site of the city.
This roundabout contains the bones of the most honorable Jalisco people in history, as well as having a beautiful garden that you can enjoy.
The beautiful kiosk that was a gift from the French Republic is a treat to see, the photos here are iconic
The venue that houses the Jalisco State Philharmonic Orchestra is a must if you come to the city
This beautiful fountain that is close to the State Shield, are one of the most beautiful points of the city
The institute that houses culture in Jalisco, is a place that you should not miss.
